# CLAUDE.md

Guidance for Claude Code (claude.ai/code) in this repo.

---

## What DomI Is

DomI = upstream **skills marketplace + governance authority** for downstream repos (`MADMESHR`, `ADMESH`, `CHILmesh`, `Health-Finance-Assistant`, `narrative-literature-review`, `Therapy_CoPi`, `ADMESH-Domains`). Changes propagate downstream via sync contract (below). No application code here.

---

## Session Start

Run on-start health check first:
```bash
bash scripts/instructions_on_start.sh
```

Checks: CLAUDE.md presence, git hygiene, skill library integrity (all `skills/*/SKILL.md` valid frontmatter), MANIFEST.md sync, open GitHub skill-request issues (auto-posts vote-threshold comments when 2+ repos voted).

**HARD STOP**: script exits non-zero with blockers (missing SKILL.md, invalid frontmatter) → resolve blocker before any write work.

### Routine session invocation directive (interim, until #83 resolves)

Until #83 consolidates per-repo session instructions, **all claude-code routine sessions must invoke these skills at documented lifecycle points**. Cross-repo default; per-repo CLAUDE.md may extend, not weaken.

| Lifecycle point | Invoke | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Bootstrap (after `instructions_on_start.sh` ✓ HEALTHY) | `bash skills/session-resume/scripts/resume.sh` | One-screen state aggregator: branch policy, DomI pin, rolling PR outstanding checkboxes, last handoff, open issues. Closes #88. Replaces ~12-tool-call manual re-discovery walk. |
| Pre-work (after issue picked) | `bash skills/check-done/scripts/scan.sh <ISSUE_N>` | Duplicate-detection scan across git log + specs/ + PRs + comments. Closes #23. |
| New-skill creation | `bash skills/skill-creator/scripts/scaffold.sh ...` | Compliant scaffold from `templates/skill.md.tmpl`. Closes #92. |
| Pre-PR / pre-merge gate (new or modified skill) | `bash skills/skill-review/scripts/audit.sh <NAME>` | 8-check policy audit (frontmatter, MANIFEST sync, benchmark, smoke, length, scripts, caveman-style, cross-refs). Closes #92. |
| Session end | `bash plugins/introspect/skills/introspect/scripts/run_introspection.sh` then commit YAML to `docs/introspections/<session_id>.md` | Per-session retro + corpus persistence. Per introspect v1.3: do NOT post retros to DomI #9 — route pains to matching skill-proposal issues via `request-from-domi`. |

**Three skills in cross-session validation:** `session-resume`, `skill-creator`, `skill-review` collect cross-session input through 2026-06-04. Invoke + report findings via standard channels (corpus + matching skill-proposal issue comments). Promotion to permanent gates on 2 weeks of cross-session input.

**Cross-repo propagation:** Directive lives here in DomI's CLAUDE.md as interim source-of-truth. When #83 ratifies consolidated session instructions across consumer repos, this section moves to `.claude/claude_routine_instructions.md`; downstream CLAUDE.md inherit by reference. Until then, downstream repos copy this table into own CLAUDE.md or read DomI's CLAUDE.md at session start.

