## Common Commands

```bash
# Install skills from a consumer repo's manifest into ~/.claude/skills/
bash scripts/install_skills.sh

# Dry-run to see what would change
bash scripts/install_skills.sh --dry-run

# Force-overwrite existing skill dirs
bash scripts/install_skills.sh --force

# Remove ~/.claude/skills/<name> that are not in the manifest (only DomI symlinks)
bash scripts/install_skills.sh --prune

# Install from a custom manifest path
bash scripts/install_skills.sh --manifest path/to/skills.manifest.json
```

No build step. Tests span surfaces (shell smokes, pytest, CI YAML lanes) — see **What "test" means in DomI** below for inventory + how to add one. "Always run before commit" check = `bash scripts/instructions_on_start.sh`.

---

## Repository Architecture

```
DomI/
├── skills/              # Vendored, versioned skills (installed to ~/.claude/skills/)
├── plugins/             # First-class Claude Code plugins (caveman, huggingface-skills,
│   │                    #   introspect, request-from-domi, sync-from-domi)
│   └── <name>/skills/<name>/  # Plugin's bundled skill (installed via plugin system)
├── scripts/
│   ├── instructions_on_start.sh   # On-start health check (DomI + consumer repo modes)
│   ├── install_skills.sh          # Manifest-driven skill installer
│   └── claude_routine_onstart.sh  # Universal onstart hook for all scheduled routines
├── .claude/claude_routine_instructions.md # Universal session prompt for scheduled routines
├── MANIFEST.md          # Source of truth: skill versions, plugin registry, sync contract
├── CODEOWNERS           # Enforces review requirements
└── .github/workflows/
    ├── repo-compliance.yml        # Branch naming, commit message, PR rules (CI hard limits)
    ├── notify-downstream.yml      # Opens sync issues in consumer repos on relevant pushes
    ├── closure-audit.yml          # Audits request: skill issue closures against framework decision
    └── sync-labels.yml            # Label synchronization
```

### Skills vs. Plugins

- **`skills/`** — Markdown-driven skills invoked as slash commands. Installed to `~/.claude/skills/` via `install_skills.sh` or symlinked from a consumer repo's `.claude/skills.manifest.json`. No plugin system required.
- **`plugins/`** — Claude Code first-class plugins installed via `claude plugin install <name>@DomI`. Three contract plugins (sync-from-domi, introspect, request-from-domi) live here. Each `plugins/<name>/` has a `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` manifest, bundles its skill at `plugins/<name>/skills/<name>/`.

### Downstream Sync Contract

Every consumer repo pins `.domi-pin` (DomI commit SHA + MANIFEST.md hash). On every push to `main` touching `skills/**`, `plugins/**`, `MANIFEST.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, or `scripts/instructions_on_start.sh`, `notify-downstream.yml` opens a `chore: sync DomI@<sha>` issue in each consumer repo. Consumer repos check `.domi-pin` at session start via `plugins/sync-from-domi/scripts/check_pin.sh` and HARD STOP on drift until `/sync from DomI` invoked.

**DomI never edits downstream files.** Contract is downstream-pulled only.

### Universal Routine Entrypoints

All scheduled Claude Code routines across repos use two DomI files as entry points:
- **`scripts/claude_routine_onstart.sh`** — curl-piped bash onstart hook
- **`.claude/claude_routine_instructions.md`** — URL-referenced session prompt (repo root, not `scripts/`)

Per-repo nuance lives in the consumer repo's own `./CLAUDE.md`, which overrides universal defaults.

---

## Git Discipline

Enforced by `repo-compliance.yml` (CI hard limits apply here + propagate as policy downstream):

**Branching — default branch `daily-maintenance`.** Every session start, check `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`. Claude Code auto-assigns `claude/*` branches — switch immediately: `git checkout daily-maintenance`. Steady state = only `main` + `daily-maintenance`. **Autonomous routines must not create branches** — push directly to `daily-maintenance`, open PR `daily-maintenance → main`. A `<type>/<slug>` PR branch (`<type>` ∈ `{fix,feat,docs,chore,refactor,test}`) reserved for operator deliberate carve-outs, requires `CLAUDE_BRANCH_OVERRIDE=1` to create via Claude Code. `branch_guard.sh` enforces the allowlist (issue #68).

**Commits:** Max 20 commits per PR. No `wip`, `fixup!`, `squash!`, `tmp`, `test commit` prefixes on main-bound PRs. Format: `<type>: <imperative summary>`, type ∈ `{fix, feat, docs, chore, refactor, test}`.

**PRs:** Single-purpose. Fill out PR template. All compliance CI checks must pass — do NOT bypass with admin merge.

**Hard stops (refuse outright):**
- Force-pushing to `main` or any shared branch
- Committing `*.env`, `*token*`, `*secret*`, `*.pem`, `*credentials*`
- Creating more than 5 branches in one session
- Using `--no-verify`, `--force`, or admin-merge to skip failures

**Git push — antipattern to avoid (issue #31):**
Single `HTTP 403` force-push rejection does NOT mean all future pushes to that branch fail. Default push = `git push origin <branch>` (fast-forward). Escalate only on real failure:
- Non-fast-forward rejection → diagnose divergence; never silently rename.
- `403` force-push blocked → confirm intent with user before renaming.
- `403` branch protected → open a PR instead.

`git push origin local:new-name` (colon-rename syntax) MUST NOT be a default workaround. Creates a new remote branch instead of updating the existing one → branch sprawl.

### Hook bypass envelope

PreToolUse / SessionStart / Stop hooks under `scripts/hooks/` enforce the policies above. Three env vars control bypass; cron sessions must leave them unset.

| Variable | Scope | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `CLAUDE_BRANCH_OVERRIDE=1` | `branch_guard.sh` only | Allow `claude/*` branch creation or write work from a non-`daily-maintenance` branch. Use for operator-deliberate carve-outs. Logged. |
| `CLAUDE_HOOK_BYPASS=hook_id[,hook_id]` | per-hook | Skip the named hook(s) for the current session. Hook IDs match the script basename without `.sh` (e.g. `branch_guard`, `commit_msg_guard`, `secret_path_guard`). Logged. |
| `CLAUDE_INTERACTIVE=1` | advisory hooks (`stop_introspect.sh`, future #11/#12) | Gate stderr output on TTY presence. Cron sessions MUST NOT set this — advisory hooks silent-skip when unset to avoid hanging on no-TTY input. |

Every bypass appends one line to `~/.claude/hook-bypass.log` (`<ISO timestamp> <hook_id> <reason>`). Log append-only; no auto-rotation. Audit trail of who overrode what + when (see issue #60 for the policy that produced this).

